# AETHER Log #22 — Documentation Runbooks, AI Integration, and WIN-CLIENT01 Ping Troubleshooting

## Summary

Today’s work focused heavily on maturing AETHER from a working homelab into a more documented, recoverable, and agent-assisted environment. Mira continued updating BookStack recovery documentation, especially around backup strategy, Nora host recovery, virtual machine recovery, Docker service recovery, Active Directory recovery, and validation checklists.

The major shift was moving documentation from general notes into operational runbooks with command safety labels, assumptions, warnings, verification steps, and recovery checklists. This created a clearer distinction between read-only checks, backup write operations, state-changing commands, and restore-only commands.

A secondary operational issue came up while working with Mira: WIN-CLIENT01 was not responding to ping. This led to troubleshooting Windows Firewall rules, network profile detection, domain authentication status, and DNS configuration.

