## Chowning Page

A humorous but useful Linux safety page was created around the phrase:

```text
Chown on there a second, cowboy.
```

The page explains `chown`, `chmod`, recursive ownership changes, and why `sudo chown -R` should be treated carefully.

Key principle:

```text
Do not chown the entire backup tree. Only chown a narrow logs or scratch folder if needed.
```

AETHER governance joke/principle:

```text
AI agents are not the system chowners.
```

This became a memorable way to reinforce a real sysadmin habit: inspect first, then modify narrowly.

